  "prompt": "Can I glue a tooth filling back into my mouth?",
  "response": "No, you should not attempt to glue a tooth filling back into your mouth. If a filling has come out, it's important to see a dentist as soon as possible. Attempting to use glue or any other adhesive can lead to further damage, infection, or complications. A dentist can properly assess the situation and provide the appropriate treatment. In the meantime, you can keep the area clean and avoid hard or sticky foods.",
